            <LEXSense LanguageCode="en" LastEdited="2021-08-17 14:10:06" LastEditedBy="">
              <DefinitionLong/>
              <DefinitionShort>a group of stars</DefinitionShort>
              <Glosses>
                <Gloss>constellation</Gloss>
              </Glosses>
              <Comments>Normally a constellation may be described as ‘a group of stars’ or ‘a family of stars’ or ‘stars that travel together’ or even ‘stars that live together.’ It is possible, however, to interpret the occurrence of ἄστρον in {S:04400704300018} as being a reference to a particular planet (namely, Saturn) rather than a constellation.</Comments>
